race.comment: Not a lot separates a few of these. PLACID PEARL (6) gets the nod after a couple of decent efforts over shorter trips to launch this prep. Finding the line well and has won up to 2200m so this journey third-up looks the right fit. HORIZONS (4) led for home and tried hard but found a couple better over 1800m at Randwick on Melbourne Cup Day. Cherry ripe after four runs back and the engagement of Hyeronimus will suit this mare's racing pattern. WOUNDER (9) last raced four weeks ago when a close fourth over 2110m at Warwick Farm. Back in trip but should settle handy and will be strong through the line. KING JERRY (5) is up in class and new to this distance but his last win at Muswellbrook by nearly six lengths stamped him as a stayer of promise. HAMMETT (2) is down in class and will keep whacking away.
